WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:04.003
♪ grandiose music playing ♪

00:08.509 --> 00:11.512
♪ theme song playing ♪

00:37.079 --> 00:39.748
♪ gentle curious music playing ♪

00:39.748 --> 00:42.459
♪ curious crescendo ♪

00:42.459 --> 00:44.962
[fire crackling]
[rocking chair creaking]

00:44.962 --> 00:46.505
Oh! Hi, kids!

00:46.505 --> 00:49.675
I'm an unlicensed hologram
of LeVar Burton.

00:49.675 --> 00:51.802
I didn't see you beam in

00:51.802 --> 00:53.846
because I had my sleep mask on.
[sleep mask beeping]

00:53.846 --> 00:57.975
Today, we're going to learn
about the wonders of books

00:57.975 --> 01:00.644
and all the fun adventures you can have

01:00.644 --> 01:03.188
watching TV shows based on them.

01:03.188 --> 01:06.525
So, throw another book on the fire
and settle in...

01:06.525 --> 01:07.776
[flame roars]

01:07.776 --> 01:11.071
...for <i>The Mystery of the Missing Mass.</i>

01:11.071 --> 01:15.033
♪ gentle mysterious music playing ♪

01:15.033 --> 01:16.451
♪ music crescendos ♪

01:17.452 --> 01:21.164
[clock chiming]

01:23.458 --> 01:25.794
[thimble tumbling]
[cursing in Chinese]

01:25.794 --> 01:27.337
I lost my thimble!

01:27.337 --> 01:28.338
♪ momentous sting ♪

01:28.338 --> 01:31.800
This sounds like a job
for Lancy Trew, girl detective!

01:31.800 --> 01:33.093
I'll look for clues.

01:33.093 --> 01:35.929
Don't look for clues!
Look for the damn thimble!

01:35.929 --> 01:38.849
No clue can hide
from my trusty flashlight!

01:38.849 --> 01:39.850
♪ momentous sting ♪

01:39.850 --> 01:42.769
[clicks flashlight]
- It's daytime, you big stupid.

01:44.396 --> 01:45.689
[clicks flashlight]

01:45.689 --> 01:46.690
♪ dramatic crescendo ♪

01:46.690 --> 01:47.774
Ah!

01:47.774 --> 01:49.818
Lancy, leave Granny alone.

01:49.818 --> 01:51.612
You know she's got severe dementia.

01:51.612 --> 01:53.989
Now, my chair's gone! [grunts]

01:53.989 --> 01:55.282
You never had a chair.

01:55.282 --> 01:58.285
What's up, Dad?
Trouble with one of your legal cases?

01:58.285 --> 01:59.661
I'm afraid so.

01:59.661 --> 02:01.455
The bank is going to foreclose

02:01.455 --> 02:04.082
on poor Farmer Pete's luxury office tower

02:04.082 --> 02:07.794
if he can't produce
the property deed by 5:00 PM.

02:07.794 --> 02:10.172
And you lost the deed
because you were drunk?

02:10.172 --> 02:11.340
I didn't lose it!

02:11.340 --> 02:14.885
I carefully hid it
along with my emergency vodka.

02:14.885 --> 02:17.262
In the old grandfather clock.

02:17.262 --> 02:18.555
♪ dramatic sting ♪

02:18.555 --> 02:21.475
[gasps]
The clock's gone! Someone stole it!

02:21.475 --> 02:25.145
This sounds like a job
for Lancy Trew, girl detective.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.522
♪ momentous sting ♪

02:26.522 --> 02:27.814
I'm countin' on ya, Lancy.

02:27.814 --> 02:31.235
You've got to find that clock by 5:00 PM.

02:31.235 --> 02:32.444
What time is it now?

02:32.444 --> 02:34.780
I don't know! The clock was stolen!

02:34.780 --> 02:38.450
♪ gentle bright music playing ♪

02:38.450 --> 02:40.577
It's my most difficult case ever.

02:40.577 --> 02:43.747
How can I look for clues before 5:00 PM?

02:43.747 --> 02:46.124
What's up, Lancy? Wanna play catch?

02:46.124 --> 02:47.709
Hi, Andi.

02:47.709 --> 02:50.087
Guys, have you met
my tomboyish friend Andi?

02:50.087 --> 02:52.798
Why can't you just call me
your <i>friend</i> Andi?

02:52.798 --> 02:54.883
Andi's on the boys' baseball team.

02:54.883 --> 02:57.344
It's just called the baseball team!

02:57.344 --> 02:58.720
Because <i>you're</i> on it.

02:58.720 --> 03:01.265
Before that, it was called
the boys' baseball team.

03:01.265 --> 03:04.351
So <i>she's</i> the boy who took my spot.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.687
♪ bright music playing ♪

03:07.688 --> 03:08.313
[grunts]

03:08.313 --> 03:11.233
♪ suspenseful music playing ♪

03:11.233 --> 03:13.235
[ball whooshing]

03:13.235 --> 03:14.236
Jeepers.

03:14.236 --> 03:17.114
Whoa!
You've got a great curveball, Andi.

03:17.114 --> 03:19.533
I mean, for a girl.
I mean, tomboy!

03:19.533 --> 03:22.077
Why don't you just say
I've got a great curveball?

03:22.077 --> 03:24.329
Why do you have to qualify it like that?

03:24.329 --> 03:26.373
I don't know.
'Cause I'm insecure?

03:26.373 --> 03:28.458
Yo, where'd the ball go?

03:28.458 --> 03:30.169
[gasps] It's gone!

03:30.169 --> 03:31.628
Someone stole it!

03:31.628 --> 03:34.798
This sounds like a job for Lancy Trew.

03:34.798 --> 03:37.217
[clicks flashlight]
And her tomboyish sidekick.

03:37.217 --> 03:38.427
[Andi grunts]
[knock]

03:38.427 --> 03:42.264
We better split up.
I'll go search the old abandoned cave.

03:42.264 --> 03:44.266
[all panting]
- I'll just...

03:44.266 --> 03:47.269
I'll handle this immediate area
right around here.

03:50.689 --> 03:51.690
[chugging soda]

03:51.690 --> 03:55.027
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

03:57.029 --> 03:58.030
♪ dramatic sting ♪

03:58.530 --> 03:59.531
♪ dramatic sting ♪

03:59.865 --> 04:00.866
♪ dramatic sting ♪

04:00.866 --> 04:03.660
Nothing but clues from
my last three cases,

04:03.660 --> 04:05.787
and no sign of the clock.
[wind blowing]

04:05.787 --> 04:07.706
♪ ominous music playing ♪

04:07.706 --> 04:09.458
[screaming]

04:10.292 --> 04:12.085
[gulping] Man.

04:12.085 --> 04:14.880
Lancy's been gone
a long [burp] time.

04:15.506 --> 04:16.798
[belches]

04:16.798 --> 04:18.550
This sounds like a job for...

04:18.550 --> 04:19.551
♪ momentous sting ♪

04:19.551 --> 04:21.803
[burp] The Smardy Boys!
- The Smardy Boys!

04:21.803 --> 04:23.138
[fire crackling]

04:23.138 --> 04:26.975
♪ gentle mysterious music playing ♪

04:27.559 --> 04:28.560
[burp]

04:28.560 --> 04:30.312
We'll start by searching everywhere,

04:30.312 --> 04:32.898
in every imaginable place.
- Right.

04:32.898 --> 04:34.816
But we'll need an automocar.

04:34.816 --> 04:36.026
[horn honking]

04:36.026 --> 04:37.569
Howdy, friends!

04:37.569 --> 04:39.488
Need a lift in my jalopy?

04:39.488 --> 04:42.241
Hey! It's our portly pal, Chud.

04:42.241 --> 04:44.826
Why can't you just
call me your pal Chud?

04:44.826 --> 04:47.746
You somehow feel obligated
to comment on my weight?

04:47.746 --> 04:50.082
[laughing] I call him Chubbo.

04:50.082 --> 04:53.252
Chud, this is Lancy's
tomboyish friend, Andi.

04:53.252 --> 04:54.503
Why?!

04:54.503 --> 04:57.256
♪ old-timey music playing ♪

04:57.256 --> 04:59.591
Mind if I change the station?

04:59.591 --> 05:01.927
- Yes.
- I wasn't talking to you.

05:01.927 --> 05:03.595
[static crackling]
MORBO [on radio]: <i>This just in!</i>

05:03.595 --> 05:06.723
<i>A wave of robberies has
struck Outskirt Village.</i>

05:06.723 --> 05:08.600
<i>Police are advising local teenagers</i>

05:08.600 --> 05:11.228
<i>to solve the crime as quickly as possible!</i>

05:11.228 --> 05:13.188
[gasps] Step on it, Chubbo!

05:13.188 --> 05:16.233
I mean, if your jalopy can
even go uphill with you in it.

05:16.233 --> 05:18.068
[laughter]

05:18.068 --> 05:21.238
Ah! That's it! I can't go on living.

05:21.238 --> 05:22.656
I'm driving off the cliff!

05:22.656 --> 05:23.699
[tires squealing]

05:23.699 --> 05:25.367
[crash]
[Andi screaming]

05:25.367 --> 05:27.286
[Bender laughing]

05:28.287 --> 05:30.080
♪ gentle bright music playing ♪

05:30.080 --> 05:31.582
[car puttering]

05:31.582 --> 05:34.501
[brakes squeal, engine cuts]
And... here we are at Lancy's house!

05:34.501 --> 05:37.087
I must've made
a wrong turn at the cliff.

05:37.087 --> 05:40.340
This whole crime wave
started with that missing clock.

05:40.340 --> 05:43.093
That's the key to solving
this mystery book!

05:43.093 --> 05:45.304
It is? Why would you think that?

05:45.304 --> 05:47.639
It's called a hunch, Chud.

05:47.639 --> 05:50.434
You sidekicks wouldn't understand.
[Andi groans]

05:50.434 --> 05:52.269
The clock was over here

05:52.269 --> 05:55.147
between these Ming vases.
[gasps]

05:55.147 --> 05:56.356
The vases are gone!

05:56.356 --> 05:57.357
♪ dramatic sting ♪

05:57.357 --> 05:59.443
And my gun is missing!

05:59.443 --> 06:01.653
My baseball mitt's gone, too!

06:01.653 --> 06:03.697
Chud, did you eat Andi's mitt?

06:03.697 --> 06:06.074
Yes, but not the other stuff!
[slurps]

06:06.074 --> 06:08.994
Shploikees! The whole house is gone!

06:08.994 --> 06:10.329
♪ dramatic sting ♪

06:10.329 --> 06:13.707
The entire town of Outskirt Village
has been stolen!

06:13.707 --> 06:15.209
[clock chiming]

06:15.209 --> 06:17.044
Wait! I found the clock.

06:17.044 --> 06:20.422
Then the criminal has
only one place left to hide.

06:20.422 --> 06:22.758
Inside that clock.

06:22.758 --> 06:25.761
Let's see who the <i>real</i> culprit is.

06:25.761 --> 06:29.181
♪ gentle suspenseful music playing ♪

06:29.181 --> 06:30.682
[all gasp]

06:30.682 --> 06:32.726
[whirring]

06:32.726 --> 06:34.061
What the hell is that?

06:34.061 --> 06:36.188
Allow me to explain.

06:36.188 --> 06:37.189
♪ momentous sting ♪

06:37.189 --> 06:39.942
It's Tom Snift, the boy inventor!

06:39.942 --> 06:42.694
Why can't you just call me the inventor?

06:42.694 --> 06:45.739
♪ abrupt dramatic music playing ♪

06:45.739 --> 06:50.202
This object is known as
a gravitational black hole.

06:50.202 --> 06:53.205
Anything that falls in can never escape,

06:53.205 --> 06:55.290
not even light itself.

06:55.290 --> 06:56.583
[whirring]
[echoing scream]

06:56.583 --> 06:59.127
[echoing]
<i>Help! Help!</i>

06:59.294 --> 07:01.171
I hear Lancy!

07:01.171 --> 07:04.007
A little sound can get out,
but that's it.

07:04.007 --> 07:07.261
Hurry! We can still save
my emergency vodka!

07:07.261 --> 07:08.595
And my daughter.

07:08.595 --> 07:10.180
[car rumbling]
- As the heroes,

07:10.180 --> 07:13.225
Biff and I will jump in
and rescue those things.

07:13.225 --> 07:14.768
You don't understand!

07:14.768 --> 07:17.271
The gravitational forces
will shred you like--

07:17.271 --> 07:20.232
[echoing pained scream]

07:20.232 --> 07:21.525
[bones rattling]

07:21.525 --> 07:25.362
There goes young Tom Snift,
off on another adventure.

07:25.362 --> 07:28.323
Chud, Andi,
you pull us out with the jalopy,

07:28.323 --> 07:30.033
so we can get all the credit.

07:30.033 --> 07:32.327
You got it, Smardy Boys.

07:32.327 --> 07:35.247
You can count on your bitter,
degraded sidekicks.

07:35.247 --> 07:36.039
[car engine starts]

07:36.039 --> 07:38.250
[both grunt, scream]

07:38.250 --> 07:40.460
[rope snaps]
[tires screech]

07:40.460 --> 07:42.129
Enjoy the hole!

07:43.088 --> 07:44.339
[Chud laughs]
[Hermes screams]

07:44.339 --> 07:47.092
[trees snapping, water splashing,
mountains rumbling]

07:49.845 --> 07:51.847
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

07:51.847 --> 07:54.099
[car engine puttering]

07:54.099 --> 07:56.143
[klaxon horn blares]

07:56.143 --> 08:00.772
Well, kids, I hope you enjoyed
watching that book as much as I did.

08:01.523 --> 08:03.567
Here's another one
I've been looking forward to

08:03.567 --> 08:05.694
because it's so short.

08:05.694 --> 08:07.196
♪ Belgian accordion music playing ♪

08:14.119 --> 08:16.622
♪ accordion music continues ♪

08:18.248 --> 08:21.251
[bicycle spokes clicking]

08:22.419 --> 08:24.046
[barking]
[rings bell]

08:25.088 --> 08:27.758
[panting]
- <i>Bonjour, mes amis!</i>

08:27.758 --> 08:30.302
[Belgian accent]
I convey the morning deliveries!

08:30.302 --> 08:32.596
<i>Bonjour</i>, young Fryfry!

08:32.596 --> 08:34.932
Ooh, I hope today is the day.

08:35.974 --> 08:38.852
Ah! Something for Captain de L'eela.

08:38.852 --> 08:42.564
[Belgian accent]
It's my, uh, medicine for my ailment.

08:42.564 --> 08:44.733
Ah, <i>oui!</i> Alcoholism.

08:44.733 --> 08:46.276
[cork pops]

08:46.276 --> 08:47.694
[chugging]

08:47.694 --> 08:49.613
Is there nothing for me?

08:49.613 --> 08:52.157
I've been waiting so many years.

08:52.157 --> 08:54.493
Alas, perhaps tomorrow.

08:54.493 --> 08:56.411
No, wait!

08:56.411 --> 09:00.082
I overlooked zis letter
for Professor Algebra,

09:00.082 --> 09:01.416
from Argentina.

09:01.416 --> 09:02.417
♪ tango sting ♪

09:02.417 --> 09:03.919
L'Argentine?

09:03.919 --> 09:05.504
[sniffing]

09:05.504 --> 09:07.923
Oh, and it's perfumed!

09:07.923 --> 09:09.424
Oh <i>hon hon hon!</i>

09:09.424 --> 09:11.927
[slurred]
<i>Who is... sended it?</i>

09:11.927 --> 09:15.639
The most beautiful songbird
I ever laid eyes on.

09:15.639 --> 09:16.723
♪ romantic music playing ♪

09:16.723 --> 09:18.433
<i>Love was in the air,</i>

09:18.433 --> 09:19.810
<i>but so was war</i>

09:19.810 --> 09:20.811
<i>and bridges.</i>

09:20.811 --> 09:21.812
Bah!

09:21.812 --> 09:24.565
<i>She fled to South America,</i>

09:24.565 --> 09:27.401
<i>the victim of unspeakable war crimes.</i>

09:27.401 --> 09:30.863
<i>Or perhaps perpetrator.
I could never get a straight answer.</i>

09:32.114 --> 09:34.616
♪ singing opera aria ♪

09:34.616 --> 09:38.078
<i>She became the most famous
opera singer in Argentina.</i>

09:38.078 --> 09:41.081
<i>"The Warbler of Buenos Aires,"
they called her.</i>

09:41.081 --> 09:42.541
♪ holding high note ♪

09:42.541 --> 09:46.253
<i>We carried on a transatlantic
romance for decades.</i>

09:46.253 --> 09:47.838
<i>Or at least I did.</i>

09:47.838 --> 09:48.922
And finally,

09:48.922 --> 09:52.050
I asked for her hand in matrimony.

09:52.050 --> 09:54.178
What she saided?

09:56.972 --> 09:58.849
Good news, <i>tout le monde!</i>

09:58.849 --> 10:01.685
[cheering]
[barking]

10:01.685 --> 10:04.855
Captain de L'eela, prepare the aeroship!

10:04.855 --> 10:07.107
♪ exciting music playing ♪

10:07.107 --> 10:09.860
[plane engines roaring]

10:09.860 --> 10:13.488
[de L'eela groaning, laughing]

10:13.488 --> 10:15.073
PROFESSOR ALGEBRA:
<i>We'll refuel in Zurich,</i>

10:15.073 --> 10:17.117
<i>Zaragoza, and Zanzibar.</i>

10:17.117 --> 10:19.745
<i>Then, take on provisions in Zaire.</i>

10:19.745 --> 10:21.496
[marker squeaking]

10:21.955 --> 10:25.542
<i>Monsieur</i>,
must you deface my finest globe?

10:25.542 --> 10:28.128
♪ exotic percussion music playing ♪

10:28.128 --> 10:30.672
One baobab fruit, please.

10:30.672 --> 10:33.217
Do you accept Belgian waffles?

10:34.885 --> 10:37.888
[bazaar chatter]

10:37.888 --> 10:39.139
[barking]

10:39.139 --> 10:40.140
[sighs]

10:40.432 --> 10:42.226
[cranking]

10:44.144 --> 10:45.771
Ruff?
♪ curious music playing ♪

10:45.771 --> 10:47.856
[whooping bark]

10:47.856 --> 10:49.691
FRYFRY:
<i>Qu'est-ce que c'est,</i> Zoidy?

10:50.317 --> 10:54.279
That is, um,
the golden crank of Khartoum.

10:54.279 --> 10:56.698
Yes, most powerful it is.

10:56.698 --> 11:00.077
They say it can crank anything!

11:00.077 --> 11:01.495
[gasps] I'll take it!

11:01.495 --> 11:04.998
Is all my money enough,
or do you want zis thing, too?

11:06.875 --> 11:08.544
♪ exciting music playing ♪

11:08.544 --> 11:11.797
[plane engines roaring]

11:12.589 --> 11:15.050
PROFESSOR ALGEBRA:
There's nowhere to land

11:15.050 --> 11:17.177
during the long ocean crossing.

11:17.177 --> 11:20.806
I just pray my magic marker holds out.

11:20.806 --> 11:23.100
Also, how's our fuel supply?

11:23.100 --> 11:25.644
[chugging] Delicious.

11:25.644 --> 11:26.937
[belches]

11:26.937 --> 11:28.939
[all scream]
[plane plummeting]

11:28.939 --> 11:31.608
[barking]
[marker squeaking]

11:32.609 --> 11:35.612
♪ tense music swelling ♪

11:37.281 --> 11:40.284
[propeller squeaking]

11:40.868 --> 11:42.202
[door creaking]

11:43.203 --> 11:47.082
Great work, Captain de L'eela!
You stuck the landing.

11:47.082 --> 11:50.169
♪ gentle regal music playing ♪

11:51.461 --> 11:55.090
Presenting the Gray Warbler
of Buenos Aires.

11:55.090 --> 11:58.468
♪ singing high opera ♪

11:58.468 --> 11:59.887
My love!

11:59.887 --> 12:03.473
You're even more
gray and warbly than I remember.

12:04.057 --> 12:05.350
[Belgian accent]
Who the 'ell are you?

12:05.350 --> 12:08.604
Your fiancé! Professor Algebra!

12:08.604 --> 12:11.273
Algebra?
Oh, for the sake of Pete!

12:11.273 --> 12:13.609
I addressed it to the wrong professor.

12:13.609 --> 12:15.986
I'm engaged to Dr. Geology now.

12:15.986 --> 12:18.488
Tough break, old man.

12:18.488 --> 12:20.490
Geology.

12:20.490 --> 12:22.034
Sorry for the confusion.

12:22.034 --> 12:25.204
You may stay for my concert
and a light meat supper.

12:25.204 --> 12:27.122
Then, scramolio!

12:27.122 --> 12:30.042
Ooh, I love it when you speak European.

12:30.042 --> 12:33.337
[passionate moaning, kissing]

12:33.337 --> 12:35.964
He will feel the wrath...

12:35.964 --> 12:37.966
of Algebra.

12:37.966 --> 12:40.844
♪ singing opera aria ♪

12:40.844 --> 12:43.805
♪

12:43.805 --> 12:46.642
♪ dramatic opera finale ♪

12:46.642 --> 12:50.229
[applause]
[panting]

12:50.229 --> 12:51.688
♪ ominous sting ♪

12:52.523 --> 12:56.193
FRYFRY: Strange.
Both professors missed the opera.

12:56.193 --> 12:58.403
[barking]

12:58.403 --> 13:01.240
[digging]
Zoidy, no! You stupid lemming!

13:01.949 --> 13:03.784
[barking]

13:03.784 --> 13:06.453
You found a bone? But, where?

13:06.453 --> 13:07.704
[footsteps shuffling]

13:07.704 --> 13:08.872
♪ dramatic sting ♪

13:08.872 --> 13:11.750
Professor Geology! Are you okay?

13:11.750 --> 13:13.752
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

13:16.171 --> 13:19.091
Where in butt's ass is my fiancé?

13:19.091 --> 13:21.218
[panting] I'm afraid...

13:21.218 --> 13:22.678
'e is dead.

13:22.678 --> 13:24.304
[gasps]

13:24.304 --> 13:26.723
I find that rather hard to believe.

13:26.723 --> 13:28.100
♪ dramatic sting ♪

13:28.100 --> 13:30.853
I can prove it, smarty pants.

13:30.853 --> 13:34.523
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

13:35.858 --> 13:37.067
[purring]

13:37.609 --> 13:38.944
My heavens!

13:38.944 --> 13:40.487
It's a priceless fossil

13:40.487 --> 13:42.698
dating to geologic antiquity!

13:42.698 --> 13:46.076
You're a priceless fossil
dating to geologic antiquity!

13:46.076 --> 13:49.746
Uh, my hat must have
blown onto it by chance,

13:49.746 --> 13:52.791
making me its official discoverer.

13:52.791 --> 13:54.418
♪ sinister music playing ♪

13:54.418 --> 13:56.670
He doesn't love you, like me.

13:56.670 --> 13:59.214
He's just here because
some valuable specimen

13:59.214 --> 14:01.175
happens to be on your property.

14:01.175 --> 14:04.469
And he's already sold off half of it.

14:04.469 --> 14:05.971
♪ dramatic sting ♪

14:05.971 --> 14:08.974
[scoffs] You fiancé-stealing bone thief!

14:08.974 --> 14:10.642
I'm calling the authorities!

14:10.642 --> 14:12.060
[European siren wailing]

14:12.060 --> 14:14.229
[tires squeal]

14:14.229 --> 14:16.773
[car doors open]
[unison footsteps]

14:16.773 --> 14:18.650
[lisping]
<i>Hola, carnitas</i> -bags.

14:18.650 --> 14:20.611
We are the Gemelos Twins,

14:20.611 --> 14:23.906
chief detectives of
the Argentinian National Police!

14:23.906 --> 14:25.782
I'm seeing double!

14:25.782 --> 14:26.783
[bottle smashes]

14:26.783 --> 14:29.119
This man is a thief, officers!

14:29.119 --> 14:32.539
That's enough evidence
for the Argentinian National Police!

14:32.539 --> 14:33.749
Lock him up, boys!

14:33.749 --> 14:35.042
Now, hold on!

14:35.042 --> 14:37.377
I may have stolen the warbler's heart,

14:37.377 --> 14:39.171
but not the missing bones.

14:39.171 --> 14:41.173
Either way, you'll die in prison.

14:41.173 --> 14:43.634
Wait! I 'ave an idea.

14:43.634 --> 14:46.386
♪ grandiose music playing ♪

14:46.386 --> 14:49.932
<i>Mon Dieu!
La</i> golden crank of Khartoum.

14:49.932 --> 14:51.308
<i>Mais oui.</i>

14:51.308 --> 14:54.436
I shall rewind ze Earth backwards in time.

14:54.436 --> 14:57.898
Then, we shall see who came
here to steal ze bones.

14:57.898 --> 15:00.651
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

15:00.651 --> 15:02.694
That'll never work.

15:02.694 --> 15:04.279
[gasps] It's working!

15:04.279 --> 15:06.448
[cranking]
One hour ago.

15:06.448 --> 15:07.824
Two hours ago.

15:07.824 --> 15:10.035
Twelve... 36...

15:10.035 --> 15:11.620
'Ow strange.

15:11.620 --> 15:13.830
No one's been 'ere for days.

15:13.830 --> 15:15.916
Weeks. Millennia!

15:15.916 --> 15:19.586
Ten million years.
A hundred million!

15:19.586 --> 15:23.590
[earth rumbling]
[barking]

15:23.590 --> 15:25.259
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

15:25.259 --> 15:27.344
[Warbler]
What the fromage is that?

15:27.344 --> 15:28.971
Africa, of course!

15:28.971 --> 15:30.430
[all gasp]

15:30.430 --> 15:32.558
Must I explain everything?

15:32.558 --> 15:34.101
Give me that globe!

15:34.101 --> 15:35.853
[crank clicking]
You see,

15:35.853 --> 15:37.896
hundreds of millions of years ago,

15:37.896 --> 15:40.399
there was only a single land mass

15:40.399 --> 15:42.401
known as Pangaea.

15:42.401 --> 15:44.945
But when the continents drifted apart,

15:44.945 --> 15:48.031
Africa separated from South America.

15:48.031 --> 15:51.827
I shall call it,
"the theory of Plate Tectonics!"

15:51.827 --> 15:54.997
Wind the continents
a smidge closer, Fryfry.

15:54.997 --> 15:57.916
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

15:57.916 --> 16:00.294
[whirring]

16:03.046 --> 16:06.008
[crashing thud]
Behold! The missing half skeleton!

16:06.008 --> 16:08.093
My word, you're right!

16:08.093 --> 16:11.054
The fossil and the fiancé are yours.

16:11.054 --> 16:13.140
You may rewind now, Fryfry.

16:13.974 --> 16:16.185
[earth rumbling]
Ah, other way!

16:16.185 --> 16:17.978
[thud]
[muffled] <i>Other way!</i>

16:17.978 --> 16:20.189
D'oops! Hang on!

16:20.189 --> 16:21.356
[earth rumbling]

16:21.356 --> 16:23.358
[squishing]

16:26.486 --> 16:28.488
[clouds whipping by]

16:29.406 --> 16:33.035
Welp! That solves the mystery
of the missing bones!

16:33.035 --> 16:35.954
What do you say, my petite warbler?

16:35.954 --> 16:37.623
Shall we give it another go?

16:37.623 --> 16:39.166
Uh, which one are you again?

16:39.166 --> 16:41.376
I don't remember.

16:41.376 --> 16:43.045
Eh, whatever. Who cares?

16:43.045 --> 16:44.713
♪ operatic singing ♪

16:44.713 --> 16:46.548
Let's go 'ome.

16:47.549 --> 16:49.968
[rumbling]

16:49.968 --> 16:52.137
♪ opera continues ♪

16:52.137 --> 16:53.305
[crash]

16:53.805 --> 16:57.559
<i>♪ Wedding March</i> by Mendelssohn playing ♪

16:57.559 --> 16:58.769
[door creaks]

16:58.769 --> 17:01.480
[barking, howls]

17:01.480 --> 17:02.481
♪ music stops abruptly ♪

17:02.481 --> 17:05.817
And they all lived happily ever after.

17:05.817 --> 17:07.486
Except that guy who died.

17:07.486 --> 17:11.031
Alright, kids.
I saved the best for last.

17:11.031 --> 17:14.201
Oh, wait. I read them out of order.
Anyway...

17:14.201 --> 17:17.204
♪ funky music playing ♪

17:20.332 --> 17:23.460
Hm. I do believe someone stole my bike.

17:23.460 --> 17:24.878
[bike squeaking, bell rings]

17:24.878 --> 17:26.088
Here's your bike back!

17:26.088 --> 17:28.674
[whoosh]
[pained yell]

17:28.674 --> 17:31.343
That solves the mystery
of the missing bike!

17:31.343 --> 17:34.513
Well, I've got another mystery
that needs solving.

17:34.513 --> 17:38.183
Which one of you is Wikipedia Brown,
the boy detective?

17:38.183 --> 17:40.519
That's me, lady. Gimme 25 cents!

17:40.519 --> 17:42.271
And I'm his bodyguard Lolly.

17:42.271 --> 17:44.565
I like to punch people. [grunts]
[groans]

17:45.524 --> 17:46.692
♪ mysterious guitar riff ♪

17:46.692 --> 17:50.404
HATTIE: <i>I had just cooked up
a fresh batch of saltwater taffy,</i>

17:50.404 --> 17:53.574
<i>so I put it on
the whatchacallit sill to cool.</i>

17:53.574 --> 17:55.951
Next thing I knew, half of it was gone!

17:55.951 --> 17:57.160
♪ dramatic guitar riff ♪

17:57.160 --> 17:59.872
Hm. This is a serious crime.

17:59.872 --> 18:01.874
It is?
[both grunt]

18:01.874 --> 18:04.501
I've got a pretty good idea who did it.

18:04.501 --> 18:07.254
Claws Pinchy and his
gang of mischief makers

18:07.254 --> 18:09.381
have been hangin' around my windowsill,

18:09.381 --> 18:11.758
lookin', whatchacallit, hungry.

18:11.758 --> 18:14.094
And now, they're at your house! Look!

18:14.094 --> 18:15.929
Don't tell me how to do my job.

18:17.306 --> 18:18.307
- Hey!
- Yo!

18:18.307 --> 18:19.349
- Ya, mon.
- Ayup.

18:19.349 --> 18:23.478
[gasps] I have solved
the mystery of the missing taffy!

18:23.478 --> 18:26.148
And it's not who you think!

18:26.148 --> 18:27.191
[ding]

18:28.192 --> 18:29.484
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

18:29.484 --> 18:32.738
At first, I suspected Claws Pinchy

18:32.738 --> 18:36.241
'cause of his leather jacket
and poor academic performance.

18:36.241 --> 18:38.619
But then, I found this clue!

18:38.619 --> 18:39.661
♪ dramatic sting ♪

18:39.661 --> 18:42.539
And that's when
my prejudices were confirmed.

18:42.539 --> 18:44.208
That could be anyone's claw!

18:44.208 --> 18:46.418
- Show me your claw.
- You mean this claw?

18:46.418 --> 18:47.669
No, the other claw!

18:47.669 --> 18:48.837
Drat!

18:48.837 --> 18:51.507
But, uh, boss, ain't you got a alibi?

18:51.507 --> 18:53.634
Uh, yeah! I was, uh, I-I-I...

18:53.634 --> 18:55.177
I was building a snowman.

18:55.177 --> 18:57.346
O-On the surface of the sun!

18:57.346 --> 18:59.014
W-With my girlfriend!

18:59.014 --> 19:02.309
The girlfriend part doesn't ring true!
Arrest him, Lolly!

19:02.309 --> 19:04.853
I can't arrest him. I'm just a kid.

19:04.853 --> 19:06.772
The best I can do is punch him.
[door opens]

19:06.772 --> 19:09.858
Now, hold on, little lady.
Let me arrest him.

19:09.858 --> 19:11.568
I'm Wikipedia's father.

19:11.568 --> 19:13.987
And also the Chief of Police.

19:13.987 --> 19:15.322
[cuffs clinking]

19:16.782 --> 19:18.200
Can I still punch him?

19:18.200 --> 19:20.369
If you don't, I will.

19:20.369 --> 19:21.495
[both grunt]

19:21.495 --> 19:25.207
♪ gentle music playing ♪

19:25.207 --> 19:26.583
What's for dinner, Mom?

19:26.583 --> 19:28.377
Boiled TV dinner.

19:30.003 --> 19:32.714
- Yum!
- How was work today, copper?

19:32.714 --> 19:34.174
I mean, dear?

19:34.174 --> 19:35.551
Smooth, baby.

19:35.551 --> 19:38.136
I sent three perps to the electric chair.

19:38.136 --> 19:41.473
Two murderers and one
unlicensed hotdog vendor.

19:41.473 --> 19:43.267
- Neat!
- But there was one crime

19:43.267 --> 19:45.894
I just couldn't solve.
- Why not?

19:45.894 --> 19:48.397
'Cause I just didn't give a damn.

19:48.397 --> 19:50.524
Maybe I could solve it and save the day.

19:50.524 --> 19:51.525
♪ dramatic sting ♪

19:51.525 --> 19:52.860
Tell me about the clues.

19:52.860 --> 19:56.071
Here's what we know.
We've had a series of complaints

19:56.071 --> 19:58.323
<i>from unsuspecting townspeople.</i>

19:58.323 --> 20:00.909
I'll be complaining about this!

20:00.909 --> 20:02.494
CHIEF BROWN:
<i>They open their doors,</i>

20:02.494 --> 20:05.998
<i>only to observe the most
shocking sight imaginable.</i>

20:05.998 --> 20:07.958
[shocked scream, weak groan]

20:07.958 --> 20:11.044
<i>A flaming bag of dog doo.</i>
[screams]

20:13.088 --> 20:17.050
I mean, it's like these bags
are appearin' out of nowhere, ya dig?

20:17.050 --> 20:19.887
I'm gonna figure out where
the flaming poo came from!

20:19.887 --> 20:23.140
Anything can be solved
if ya find the clues.

20:23.140 --> 20:25.350
[doorbell ringing]
I'll get it!

20:25.350 --> 20:26.518
[door opens]
[fire crackling]

20:26.518 --> 20:29.521
[screams, grunts]
[stamping, squishing flaming bag]

20:29.521 --> 20:30.689
Found one!

20:30.689 --> 20:33.108
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

20:33.108 --> 20:35.402
Where were you Friday at 2:00 PM?

20:35.402 --> 20:38.864
In your garage, talkin' to you,
you id-jit!

20:38.864 --> 20:39.948
That checks out.

20:39.948 --> 20:41.742
Alls I know is I was

20:41.742 --> 20:44.578
loiterin' in an alley
with the other local toughs,

20:44.578 --> 20:46.580
smokin' a lollipop.

20:47.414 --> 20:48.624
[exhales]

20:48.624 --> 20:50.918
I'm a kid with a magnifying glass.

20:50.918 --> 20:53.670
Got any clues I can magnify?
- Indeed!

20:53.670 --> 20:56.840
I saved the slipper
I used to stomp the doo.

20:57.841 --> 20:59.760
Ugh! What else you got?

20:59.760 --> 21:02.846
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

21:02.846 --> 21:04.264
Case closed, folks!

21:04.264 --> 21:07.893
I pretended to look for clues,
but we all know it was...

21:07.893 --> 21:09.436
Claws Pinchy!

21:09.436 --> 21:10.938
♪ dramatic sting ♪

21:10.938 --> 21:14.107
I'm afraid he's got
the ultimate alibi, son.

21:14.107 --> 21:17.194
He went to the chair for that taffy caper.

21:17.945 --> 21:21.448
That's the way to go. Sittin' down.

21:21.448 --> 21:23.075
What a strange case.

21:23.075 --> 21:25.452
I've never found so many clues before.

21:26.119 --> 21:29.623
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

21:31.124 --> 21:32.459
CHIEF BROWN:
Ah yeah.

21:32.459 --> 21:35.295
That's some mass-murderer-level stuff.

21:35.295 --> 21:37.923
So, did you solve the mystery?

21:37.923 --> 21:41.134
I... I... No! [crying]

21:41.134 --> 21:43.762
It all adds up to nothing!

21:43.762 --> 21:45.597
I thought I could solve anything,

21:45.597 --> 21:47.599
but we will never, ever know

21:47.599 --> 21:50.686
where the flaming doo-doo came from!

21:50.686 --> 21:52.396
I know where it came from.

21:52.396 --> 21:53.397
♪ bright sting ♪

21:53.397 --> 21:54.982
Neil deGrasse Tyson?

21:54.982 --> 21:56.900
May I borrow your magnifying glass?

21:56.900 --> 21:58.902
Hell no! I don't know you!

21:58.902 --> 22:01.196
I'm not lendin' you my magnifying glass!

22:01.196 --> 22:03.824
That's okay. I brought
an electron microscope.

22:05.534 --> 22:06.994
[beeping, whirring]

22:06.994 --> 22:09.580
Take a closer look at this soiled bag

22:09.580 --> 22:11.206
from your wall of clues.

22:11.206 --> 22:13.166
- No, thanks.
- I said look!

22:13.166 --> 22:14.459
What's it made of?

22:14.459 --> 22:16.253
- Paper?
- Poop?

22:16.253 --> 22:18.213
A combination thereof?

22:18.213 --> 22:21.884
[dial clicking]
NEIL: It's made entirely of matter!

22:21.884 --> 22:24.595
And that's the clue I needed
to solve the mystery.

22:24.595 --> 22:28.056
But, how did it end up on my doorstep?

22:28.056 --> 22:29.933
Yeah. Where'd it come from?

22:30.642 --> 22:34.897
You see,
approximately 13.8 billion years ago,

22:34.897 --> 22:39.109
all matter was created in the Big Bang.

22:39.109 --> 22:43.030
So, that's where it came from.
The Big Bang.

22:43.030 --> 22:45.866
Of course! It was so obvious!

22:45.866 --> 22:48.243
[murmuring in agreement]

22:48.243 --> 22:49.953
But wait a minute.

22:49.953 --> 22:52.623
Where were <i>you</i> when the Big Bang happened?

22:52.623 --> 22:54.124
Me? I...

22:54.124 --> 22:56.126
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

22:56.126 --> 22:58.170
It was the Big Bang guy! Get him!

22:58.170 --> 22:59.671
Gotta go! [panting]

22:59.671 --> 23:01.924
♪ tense music playing ♪

23:01.924 --> 23:03.217
[doorbell ringing]

23:03.217 --> 23:05.677
Hang on. Let me get the door.
[flames whoosh]

23:07.513 --> 23:10.224
Neil deGrasse Tyson?
- Yeah, yeah, listen.

23:10.224 --> 23:13.185
You got a place I can hide
where no one ever goes?

23:13.185 --> 23:14.978
Sure! Right over here.

23:17.439 --> 23:19.858
Well, that's all for today, kids.

23:19.858 --> 23:22.277
And remember, in space,

23:22.277 --> 23:25.364
no one can hear you read.
[shuts door]

23:27.366 --> 23:28.367
[LeVar and Neil grunt]

23:28.367 --> 23:30.202
♪ grandiose music playing ♪

23:33.247 --> 23:36.250
♪
